The <strong><code>width</code></strong> CSS property sets an element's width. By default, it sets the width of the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Box_Model/Introduction_to_the_CSS_box_model#content-area">content area</a>, but if <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/box-sizing" title="The box-sizing CSS property sets how the total width and height of an element is calculated."><code>box-sizing</code></a> is set to <code>border-box</code>, it sets the width of the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Box_Model/Introduction_to_the_CSS_box_model#border-area">border area</a>.